  "instructions": [
    "Rinse sugar snap peas and pat them dry.",
    "Preheat oven to 200°C.",
    "Toss peas with olive oil and tandoori spice mix, then spread on a baking sheet.",
    "Roast peas for 7-8 minutes until slightly charred.",
    "Let peas cool to room temperature.",
    "Whisk Greek yogurt, lemon juice, honey, salt, pepper, and a pinch of red chili flakes in a bowl.",
    "Fold cooled peas into the dressing, then stir in dill, scallions, and toasted sesame seeds.",
    "Serve chilled or at room temperature, garnishing with extra dill if desired."
